-- Wells Fargo faces payout after $54.8 million loan fee verdict
-- By Nate Raymond in New York
-- Fri Dec 19, 2014 01:59PM EST
-- None



NEW YORK, Dec 19 (Reuters) - Homeowners suing mortgage companies once owned by a bank Wells Fargo & Co <WFC.N> later acquired won a nearly $54.8 million verdict on Friday in a class action over excessive fees.

